body.name: Nuwave Healthy Duralon Blue Ceramic Nonstick Cookware Set, Diamond Infused Scratch-Resistant, PFAS Free, Dishwasher & Oven Safe, Induction Ready & Evenly Heats, Tempered Glass Lids & Stay-Cool Handles

features: PREMIUM FORGED CONSTRUCTION – Forging makes the cookware strong and durable yet lightweight and easy to handle. It is a work-of-art where form meets function. It is constructed to perform well under any situation at any skill level.

HEALTHY DURALON BLUE COATING – The eco-friendly, ultra-non-stick Gen10 Duralon Blue is all-natural ceramic coating free of harmful chemicals like PFAS*, PTFE, PFOA, lead, and cadmium. It also does not emit toxic gases at higher temperatures. *Tested by TÜV Rheinland for 106 known PFAS elements and none were detected.

GENERATION 10 (G10) CERAMIC – For more than a decade, we have continuously perfected our Duralon Ceramic Coating. G10 Duralon Blue is exceptional in every category. It heats fast and evenly; releases food effortlessly; and is extraordinarily durable.

DURALON BLUE HARDNESS – Hardness is rated at 9H. Since diamond is rated at 10H, It is extremely strong. It has HIGH resistances to abrasion, corrosion, and acid meaning it won’t chip or discolor and will retain its non-stick properties longer.

INDUCTION READY & EVEN HEAT DISTRIBUTION – Every cookware is bonded and reinforced with anti-warp SS plate on the bottom to make it induction ready. This bonding delivers fast, even heat distribution, and superior heat retention at any temperature.

ALL COOKTOP & OVEN SAFE – Every piece of the cookware set is also safe for use on all cooktops including electric and gas stoves. They’re oven-safe up to 500°F for seamless transition from stove to oven.

ERGONOMIC STAY-COOL SS HANDLES – The handles are stainless steel, ergonomic, anti-fatigue, lightweight yet sturdy. Handles of pans are with heat diffuser built in to keep the grip cooler.Note: please hold the farest end of fry pans/saucepans to avoid burned. Always use oven mitts or pot holders when handling stockpots.

PREMIUM TEMPERED GLASS LIDS – The premium shatter-resistant lids included with this set include a small ventilation opening to ensure steam is released safely while you’re cooking. Plus, they are oven safe up to 350°F and dishwasher safe.
10-YEAR WARRANTY - Get the peace of mind knowing that every piece of your cookware is covered with the 10-year limited manufacturer warranty.

WHAT’S INCLUDED – 1.5 qt. saucepan with lid; 2 qt. saucepan with lid; 3 qt. saucepan with lid; 5 qt. stock pot with lid; 8 qt. stock pot with lid; 8” fry pan; 9.5” fry pan. Every piece is treated with the revolutionary Duralon Blue Ceramic Coating.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love at first saute!
reviews.reviewText: This set is as beautiful as it is durable. They came packaged well, all individually wrapped and protected. I have been hesitant to buy non-stick cookware due to the chemicals, but Nuwave has none of them. It is truly non-stick, I have not had to add oils or sprays. They work great and clean up easily. It says they are dishwasher safe, but I think they will last longer if hand washed, which is my preference. I've had stainless pots and pans for 20 years, hating how everything stuck. So happy I bought these and would recommend them to everyone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My wife and I have been using these for over a month now. We selected these because of the ceramic non-stick coating and because of the fact that the pans have a stainless steel base.We are very pleased with how easy they are to clean and we’ve not had any stains on an outer surface. We feel the 5 pans are a good value for the price. I like the “solid” weight feel of the pans. The material seems thicker than most aluminum pans plus these have a stainless steel bottom that adds weight and durability. Our stovetop is gas.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best cookware I’ve owned
reviews.reviewText: There are no dislikes with this set! I bought the vanilla cream, beautiful! I don’t have to use oil or butter just use a little water on the bottom and that’s all you need to avoid sticking. So easy to clean-everything (it’s seems like I am washing a clean pan since nothing sticks. I love that the bottom doesn’t stain! Love the sturdiness of the set. Lids are great with the steam release. Can’t say enough about the greatness of this product. Worth the money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy clean up!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had these pans for about 4 months now and they have held up pretty well. They are super easy to clean. Even though it does say that it’s dishwasher safe, hand washing is recommended. But I don’t mind washing it by hand because it’s is very easy to clean. I haven’t had any issues with food sticking on it. And they look great! Now for the cons. I noticed the coating coming off on the rim, the part where the lid sits on the pot. That’s kind of unfortunate. And the handles are not ergonomic. The edges are uncomfortable to hold. But it’s not a deal breaker for me. All in all, these pots are great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I’m in love
reviews.reviewText: I Love this pot/pan set! The non stick coating works well. I only have to spray when I’m frying eggs 😁 everything else so far has come out of pan very well. And they are easy to clean- a big plus to save time in the kitchen. The color is beautiful and durable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: When asked what I wanted for Christmas, I said "a good set of pots and pans". My husband agreed. We had a hodgepodge of unmatched pans that everything stuck to. I reviewed a ton of sets before settling on the Nuwave pans. I LOVE THESE PANS!!!! Nothing sticks. They are heavy, not some cheap aluminum ones that warp. Today I made chili. EVERY pot I used before, ended up with burnt beans on the bottom. Not this set! It simmered all day and when I served it, everything was perfect. Nothing burnt on the bottom. When I emptied the pot, it cleaned up like a dream. I can't say enough about them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Surprisingly high quality and looks for an inexpensive set.
reviews.reviewText: We bought these because they work on an inductive cooktop, but also work on gas and standard electric burners. Compared to our Cuisinart pots, many of which are 37 years old and still excellent, these are surprisingly nice: Thick bottom (better for even heating) and walls, a finish that seems very solid, and a tough non-stick interior. Hint: Don't believe that hype that you don't need oil or margarine and the foot will just slip out--but with a squirt of Pam, it will, easily. Glass lids are a toss-up, but we generally prefer them because you can see what's going on, yet you must treat them carefully. You must use non-metallic utensils but most people do anyway.So far, we're thrilled with them!
